[thinking] I'm considering separating from the opengauss library behavior. It might be better to use natural library classes for "active class only" reports. For ObjectFactory, it's supposed to create custom implementations, while helper classes can stay valid. Generated test classes have inner classes, and a one-to-one mapping seems acceptable. I need to think about potential issues with reflection under native. It seems I should adapt the existing PostgreSQL test since it likely passed due to metadata, whereas opengauss doesn't have that. Updating metadata might be necessary for testing coverage with DefaultJavaSSLFactory.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Analyzing test execution**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think tests should run under Native Image by default. If there's a failure due to SSL defaults, that's problematic. It seems less likely with helper classes since they don't have external side effects. I need to grasp the TCK better. Perhaps I can verify resources that are generated but not committed for each run, given the existing untracked build. If the external workflow runs the agent first, Native Image works. But what if they compile with ./gradlew nativeTestCompile without an agent? That might cause issues with ObjectFactory tests unless the test reflection metadata is generated.
